<HEADLINE> China's Pang Upsets Lines in China Snooker International </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 8 (Xinhua) -- China's wild card Pang Weiguo
came out with an upset in the first-day competition of the China
International snooker tournament as he beat England's Peter Lines
5-1 on Monday here.
</P>
<P>
This is the first world-ranking snooker tournament held in
China. All the top-ranking players, including reigning world
champion and world number one John Higgins, Stephen Hendry and
Ronnie O'Sullivan, will appear in the tournament.
</P>
<P>
Pang, 26, the No.1 snooker of the country in 1998, made a 3-0
lead against his opponent, who ranks 53rd in the world, and kept
his form for an good start of the tournament.
</P>
<P>
All the other three Chinese wild cards fell in the first-day
nine competitions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
