<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israeli Port Workers' Strike Causes Huge Losses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, March 8 (Xinhua) -- The nine-day-long Israeli port
worker's strike has caused huge economic losses to the country,
and port authorities and manufacture associations have asked the
government to help end the strike.
</P>
<P>
Officials of the port authorities told the Israel Radio on
Monday that during the past nine days, 58 large cargo ships were
forced to leave Israel without unloading due to the work stoppage
and about 500 million U.S. dollars of material and supplies could
not reach Israel.
</P>
<P>
Due to the strike, many Israeli companies and factories are
facing shortage of supplies and some of them are on the verge of
close-down, the officials said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, port authorities and representatives from several
local companies and factories on Monday urged Prime Minister
Benjamin Netanyahu to help end this strike.
</P>
<P>
Supported by the Israeli National Trade Unions, the port
workers are striking for salary increase, but so far their
demands are not met. 
</P>
</TEXT>
