<HEADLINE> Indian, US Officials Hold Talks in New Delhi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, March 8 (Xinhua) -- Indian and U.S. officials held
consultations here Monday on a wide range of issues, including
regional, international and bilateral issues of mutual concerned,
official sources here disclosed.
</P>
<P>
The American team was led by Deputy Assistant Secretary for
East Asia Susan Shirke, who arrived here from Beijing where she
had assisted U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright during her
recent visit to China.
</P>
<P>
The consultations came after the eighth round of Indo-U.S.
talks on non-proliferation between Indian External Affairs
Minister Jaswant Singh and U.S. Deputy Secretary of State Strobe
Talbott on January 29 in New Delhi. 
</P>
