<HEADLINE> 14 Opposition Commanders Join Taliban: Radio Kabul </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 8 (Xinhua) -- Fourteen opposition commanders
in Afghanistan along with their men have changed side to support
the Taliban militia, Radio Kabul reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, the commanders along with hundreds of
their followers decided to join hands with the Taliban during
their meeting with the governor of Ghor province Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The commanders pledged that they will spare no efforts to serve
their countrymen and defend the objectives and aims of the Taliban
regime, the radio added.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, according to Radio Tehran, the Taliban recaptured
Dara-e-Soof district in Northern province of Samangon from the
forces led by former defense minister Ahmed Shah Masood. 
</P>
