<HEADLINE> Botswana Inflation Surges to 7.2 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, March 8 (Xinhua) -- Botswana's year-on-year
inflation surged to 7.2 percent in February from 6.5 percent in
January, rising for the fourth month in a row, South African Press
Association reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The cost of living index stood at 117.3 points in February,
against a base of 100 in November 1996. This represented a rise of
0.9 percent compared with January, SAPA said.
</P>
<P>
The increase is due to rises in prices of food, fuel, power and
 household operations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
