<DOCNO> XIE19990309.0014 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Eritrea to Host Regional Football Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ASMARA, March 8 (Xinhua) -- An Eritrean youth leader confirmed
in Asmara Monday that his country will host this year's
Confederation of East and Central Africa Football Associations
(CECAFA) Youth Championship.
</P>
<P>
Chairman of the National Union of the Eritrean Youth and
Students, Mohiadin Shengeb, also revealed that Ethiopia would not
participate in the games.
</P>
<P>
He noted that Ethiopia refused to play with the Eritrean team
in the Cairo games last year.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, reports said that the venue of the football games
might have to be shifted to either Kenya, Zanzibar or Uganda
because of the escalating war between Ethiopia and Eritrea.
</P>
<P>
The event is scheduled to take place in Eritrean capital Asmara
from April 10 to 24. Kenya, Uganda, Burundi, Somalia and Sudan
were reported to have confirmed their participation.
</P>
<P>
However, there is no sign showing that an immediate cease-fire
could be reached between the two Horn of Africa neighbors whose
relations have soured since the outbreak of fight over a contested
390-square-kilometer rocky area called Badme southwest of the
capital 10 months ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
