<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe's New Constitution to Be Ready By </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, March 8 (Xinhua) -- The drafting of Zimbabwe's new
constitution could be completed by November this year, Minister
Without Portfolio Eddison Zvobgo said Monday in Bulawayo, the
country's second largest city.
</P>
<P>
Addressing participants at a media and constitution workshop,
Zvobgo, who is also ruling Zanu (PF) legal affairs secretary, said
he was confident the draft constitution could be written
thoroughly within a short period of time.
</P>
<P>
"We would like the constitution to be completed this year and
elections to take place under the new constitution," he said.
</P>
<P>
