<HEADLINE> UK Fast Food Chains Reject GM Foods: Survey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 8 (Xinhua) -- Opposition to genetically modified
(GM) food is growing in the UK with almost half of Britain's
leading fast food chains dropping GM ingredients from their
products.
</P>
<P>
Three fast food chains, Wimpy, Pizza Express and Domino Pizza,
say they have already dropped it and others intend to be GM free
soon, according to a new survey published Monday by Friends of the
Earth.
</P>
<P>
In the survey Friends of the Earth asked the 11 biggest fast
food chains in Britain which have 3,548 outlets across the country
whether they were going to remove GM ingredients from food they
sold.
</P>
<P>
The answers showed that three of the chains, Wimpy, Pizza
Express and Domino Pizza, already believe they don't sell any more
products containing GM ingredients.
</P>
<P>
Burger King and KFC said that they were in the process of
removing all GM ingredients from their products while McDonald's
and Perfect Pizza said they were currently considering going
GM-free. 
</P>
