<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canada's Employment In Public Sector Stabilizes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, March 8 (Xinhua) -- After five years of job cuts,
Canada's employment in the public sector started to stabilize last
year, falling only 0.6 percent from 1997, Statistics Canada
reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Governments employed an average of 2.8 million people last
year, a drop of about 15,400 jobs from the previous year. That was
the smallest drop since 1993.
</P>
<P>
In comparison, the public sector lost 88,000 jobs in 1996 and
70,000 in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Public employees also saw their pay rise for the first time in
five years, with an overall increase of 0.6 percent, said the
federal agency.  
</P>
</TEXT>
