<HEADLINE> Zeneca Consolidates Its Business in Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON March 8 (Xinhua) - Zeneca, UK's pharmaceuticals giant,
Monday announced the move to 100 percent ownership of Zeneca
Pharma Asiatic Limited, its sales and marketing joint venture in
Thailand.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture company, in which the Zeneca holding was 49
percent, was established in 1996 with headquarter in Bangkok.
</P>
<P>
Prior to that time Zeneca conducted its pharmaceuticals
operations in Thailand using East Asiatic (Thailand) Public
Company Ltd as its agency.
</P>
<P>
Potential pharmaceutical sales in Thailand for 1999 are
expected to be in the region of 650 million US dollars of which
Zeneca currently has a share of 0.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
John Patterson, Territorial Business Director for Zeneca
Pharmaceuticals said: "The move to 100 percent ownership is the
next logical step for Zeneca in Thailand."
</P>
<P>
Over the last few years Zeneca has moved steadily to develop
its pharmaceuticals business in the Far East with many new
subsidiaries have been set up.  
</P>
