formations of F-14, F-15 and F-16 warplanes supported by early
warning AWACS from the Turkish airspace violated Iraqi airspace
over Neineva, Erbil and Dohuk provinces.
</P>
<P>
These warplanes shelled civilian targets and anti-aircraft
artillery positions, injuring one Iraqi citizen, he said. He did
not say whether the injured is a military personnel or a
civilian. (BC-Iraq-US-Raids)
</P>
<P>
