prepared for the first round of training.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia is implementing a five-year educational program
between 1997 and 2001. The five-year program has plans to raise
primary enrollment from 3.1 to seven million, thus achieving an
average gross enrollment ratio of 50 percent for primary education
in the country. Some 58,000 new teachers would be trained while
those currently on the job will be given skill up- grading
trainings. 
