<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Telecom, Microsoft to Develop Broadband On-line Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 9 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's major full-service
communications provider Hongkong Telecom and American software
giant Microsoft announced here today strategic cooperation to
develop high-speed broadband services that will allow Hong Kong to
fully experience the convergence of low-cost personal computer and
telecommunications technologies.
</P>
<P>
The joint effort, announced by Hongkong Telecom Chief Executive
Linus W. L. Cheung and visiting Microsoft Chairman and CEO Bill
Gates at a press conference, is expected to usher in an era of
technology convergence for a new lifestyle in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Cheung said at the press conference that the two companies will
be developing "very exciting applications to stimulate the usage
of the PCs and their applications."
</P>
<P>
He said Hongkong Telecom can provide high-speed Internet which
is 30 to 300 times faster than normal Internet and ... "it is very
important we create applications like turning PCs into interactive
TVs."
</P>
<P>
"I hope this partnership of cooperation will not only set an
example for Hong Kong, breaking new markets, but for the world."
</P>
<P>
Gates said Hong Kong is in a "very privileged position" because
of the companies that add up the Internet to the PCs and the
investment that has been made to the existing network.
</P>
<P>
"There is a chance to really lead the way to show the
applications of how businesses will be done in the years ahead,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
Describing the joint project as a "milestone," Gates said, "We
see ourselves as really giving the businesses here in Hong Kong a
platform to be created with... and to address the entire market."
</P>
<P>
With the project, home PC users will be able to view exciting
movie titles and view these on their PCs or on their TVs -- just
by browsing through titles of the latest movies, while at the same
time having access to the wealth of information available on the
Internet.
</P>
<P>
Users will be able to communicate with their friends via live
video conferencing, participate in voice or on-line chat rooms,
send and receive e-mail, check the latest news, go shopping and
conduct secure e-commerce transactions.
</P>
<P>
Students will be able to interact and share in the learning
experience in new and unique ways.
</P>
<P>
Businesses will benefit from new and advanced solutions and
applications hosted and available through Hongkong Telecom's
broadband network, while also gaining access to an entirely new
class of video-enabled applications including video conferencing
and training-on-demand.
</P>
<P>
The innovative services will run on a tightly integrated
Microsoft platform which will accommodate a wide spectrum of
existing service components and capital assets.
</P>
<P>
The new applications scheduled to be implemented include video
on demand, music on demand, software on demand, up-to-the-minute
news and game zone.
</P>
<P>
The new application will be added up to the existing and the
world's first interactive TV and high-speed Internet service,
launched by the Hongkong Telecom a year ago.  
</P>
</TEXT>
