<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, March 9 (Xinhua) -- Lao Minister of Information and
Culture Sileua Bounkham has called for efforts to ease the impact
of inflation on Laos' economic growth, people's living conditions
and foreign investment, according to a report by Laos' news agency
KPL Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
KPL quoted Sileua Bounkham as saying that the causes of the
inflation in Laos stemmed from the economic and monetary crisis in
the region, from the failure in agricultural production caused by
natural disasters, and the imbalance between the lack of
production capability and high demands of social consumption,
among others.
</P>
