<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lawmakers, Advisors on Governing China According to Law (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Another CPPCC National Committee member Wang Xiang pointed to
the fact that China is now building a socialist market economy,
the main features of which are a standardized market and an
orderly and fair competitive mechanism.
</P>
<P>
"All these features require the protection of a unified and
comprehensive legal system," said Wang, a private business manager.
</P>
<P>
According to NPC deputy Lu Zhiguang, the principle of "
governing the country according to law" will safeguard the
independent and equal legal status for all economic entities in
the market, protect property ownership and contract freedom, and
promote social justice and righteousness.
</P>
<P>
"It is all because of its early and successful promotion of the
rule of law that Guangdong, on the forefront of China's reform and
opening-up, has fully safeguarded its achievements in reform and
opening-up and maintained a sustainable economic development,"
said Lu, vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the Guangdong
Provincial People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
Law experts here say that the principle of "governing the
country according to law" is a direct reflection of China's shift
from a central planned economy to a market-driven economy.
</P>
<P>
They also note that the endorsement of this principle is a
large project involving people of all walks of life and sectors
across the country and a lot of issues, which include legislation,
law enforcement, judicial justice and supervision, and promotion
of legal knowledge and people's law-abiding awareness.
</P>
<P>
"This principle is key to the smooth implementation of a series
of measures to be adopted soon by the government for the deepening
of reforms," an expert stressed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
