<HEADLINE> Fight Corruption to Ensure Project Quality: CPPCC Members </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 9 (Xinhua) -- Members of the Ninth National
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC), who are here attending the second session of
the CPPCC, expressed their strong discontent over enormous
economic losses caused by shoddy engineering projects.
</P>
<P>
They urged to step up legal action and eliminate corruption to
ensure the quality and safety of the engineering projects.
</P>
<P>
According to official figures, over the past few years, such
accidents have led to a combined economic loss of around 100
billion yuan and 20 percent of the engineering projects built in
the period failed to reach the quality standards.
</P>
<P>
In his speech, Bai Dahua, a vice-chairman of the Central
Committee of the China Democratic National Construction
Association, said that poor management has caused a series of
accidents in engineering projects recently, which shows that
people pay little attention to quality, do not abide by law, and
the construction market is not ripe, which has provided a "
greenhouse" for corruption.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, of the over 100,000 bribery
cases handled by procuratorates in recent years, 63 percent are
related to the construction business.
</P>
<P>
Infrastructure projects of poor quality may turn into disasters,
he said, urging people from all walks of life to be vigilant
against the problem of poor quality engineering projects.
</P>
<P>
He proposed to raise the awareness of the public about the rule
of law and the sense of quality, rectify the construction market,
crack down on unlawful activities in the field, and mobilize
people from all circles to take part in supervision in this regard.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on behalf of non-party-affiliation CPPCC members,
Professor Liu Xila, from the Beijing-based Qinghua University,
said that the issue of quality and security for engineering
projects require the joint efforts by people from engineering
management, educational and law circles.
</P>
<P>
The government departments in charge of engineering management
should take the first responsibility to deal with the issue, he
said, adding that at present, the most important is to regularize
the construction market, adopt the policy of open biddings and
contract, and accept the supervision of the news media.
</P>
</TEXT>
