Vancouver last Tuesday. Police confirmed the search was connected
to an investigation into a gambling club allegedly operated by the
premier's friend and neighbor, Dimitrios Pilarinos.
</P>
<P>
Despite the search, police said the premier is not suspected of
any wrongdoing, according to the newspaper.
</P>
<P>
Clark said the RCMP search of his home had been "very
frightening." The only thing police had taken from his home after
a 45-minute search were copies of his house plans, he added.
</P>
