<BODY>
<HEADLINE> People's Daily on Tibet (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In 1957, the central government decided not to make the reforms
in Tibet during the Second Five-Year Plan period (1958-1962) and
to allow the local government in Tibet make its own decision about
reforms in accordance with local conditions.
</P>
<P>
But, a few upper class reactionaries at heart were against the
reforms and tried to guard the theocratic feudal system and the
interests of the three categories of feudal lords by raising an
armed rebellion for Tibetan independence. After this rebellion was
quelled, the central government decided to comply with the wishes
of the Tibetan people and implement the democratic reforms.
</P>
<P>
The Tibetan upper class reactionaries had tried to turn the
conflict between the new and old systems into a war between ethnic
groups, but the Tibetan people, who had spent eight years waiting
and watching, took the side of the Communist Party of China and
the People's Liberation Army without any hesitation.
</P>
<P>
The democratic reforms helped surfs become the masters of their
own destiny and there are no manorial lords or surfs today and
people are no longer sold, traded, given, or mortgaged as property,
nor are they separated into several categories or classes, and
there is no more gouging out of eyes, cutting off of feet or hands
or tongues.
</P>
<P>
The democratic reforms were a glorious chapter in the history
of global human rights in the 20th century.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990309.0098 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> People's Daily on Tibet (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In 1965, the Tibet Autonomous Region was established and the
Tibetan people became the masters of their own system of regional
autonomy.
</P>
<P>
Over the past 40 years, especially since China's reforms and
opening-up began in 1978, The Tibetan people have developed
agricultural and industrial production, got away from poverty, and
built up fortunes with the support of the central government and
people in the rest of China, and enormous changes have taken place
in Tibet.
</P>
<P>
The Tibetan economy has grown faster than the rest of the
country on average since 1994 and the standard of living and
health of the Tibetan people have improved considerably.
</P>
<P>
The fulfillment of the goals of the democratic reforms and the
achievements made in the 40 years of socialist construction in
Tibet have shown that the democratic reforms and socialist system
and the abolition of the serf system were the correct decisions of
the Tibetan people and the only way to develop Tibet and make it
prosper. Any attempt to return Tibet to serfdom will be in vain.
</P>
<P>
Everyone knows that Tibet has been an inalienable part of China
under effective central government rule since it was merged with
Chinese territory in the Yuan Dynasty (1271-1368), but Dalai Lama,
in his 40 years of exile, has stuck to his reactionary position
and involved himself in activities that are intended to divide the
country.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
