<HEADLINE> Tianjin Hosts Sino-Russian Trade Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, March 9 (Xinhua) -- Trade talks between China and the
Novosibirskayath in the Russian Federation were held today in
Tianjin, a major port city in north China.
</P>
<P>
Some 100 businessmen from Novosibirskayath and a number of
Chinese representatives attending the '99 Tianjin Import and
Export Products Fair participated in the talks which focused
mainly on the high-technology cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Novosibirskaya is the most important industrial, technological
and cultural center in east Russia, businessmen from there are
attending the fair to exhibit a wide array of products, including
laser appliances, electric machinery and optical electronics.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin has opened air links with the Russian Novosibirskaya
and both sides anticipate broad prospects for cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the trade volume between Tianjin and
Russia has surged to 100 million US dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
