<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CPPCC Member Calls for Early Solution for Taiwan Question </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 9 (Xinhua) -- A top advisor to the Chinese
government called for an early solution to the Taiwan question
here today.
</P>
<P>
Zheng Lizhi, a member of the country's top advisory body, the
national committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference, and a member of the standing committee of the Taiwan
Democratic Self-Government League Central Committee, made the call
at a speech meeting of the ongoing session of the CPPCC national
committee.
</P>
<P>
"With Hong Kong having returned to the embrace of the
motherland and Macao also coming back, the problem of Taiwan is
becoming increasing prominent," Zheng said.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin has put forward an eight-point proposal
on developing relations across the Taiwan Strait and promoting a
peaceful reunification of the motherland. And his suggestion to
end hostility and start negotiations under the principle of "One
China" in a report at the 15th Party Congress also created
favorable conditions for solving the problem of Taiwan peacefully
and promoting relations across the Taiwan Strait, Zheng said.
</P>
<P>
A peaceful reunification of the motherland still faces many
obstacle, he said. "The principal leader of the Taiwan authorities
has deviated from the principle of 'one China', and got involved
in activities aimed at creating 'two Chinas'. He has also
connived at the development of pro-'Taiwan independence' forces
and obstructed reunification of the two sides across the Taiwan
Strait," he said.
</P>
<P>
Taiwan is part of China, he said. The attempt to change this
fact through a referendum in Taiwan does not accord with the
interests of the Taiwan people, he said, adding "this is playing
with fire."
</P>
<P>
"A peaceful reunification is where the fundamental interests of
the Chinese people lie," Zheng said, citing numerous favorable
factors and conditions for the final solution of the Taiwan
question such as the same origin of the people, complementary and
mutually-beneficial economies on both sides, and expanding
exchanges across the Taiwan Strait.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the principle of "on country,two systems"
is based on a respect for realities in Taiwan, which will be able
to maintain its capitalist system and way of life after the
reunification, just as Hong Kong has done after its return to the
motherland.
</P>
<P>
Zheng stressed that the Chinese people will not permit anti-
China forces to contain China by thwarting the reunification of
China. "Both sides across the Taiwan Strait should conduct talks
and negotiations and fight against interference by foreign forces,
so as to achieve the reunification of the motherland as early as
possible and enjoy together the dignity and honor of a great
nation," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
