<HEADLINE> Spring Snow Relieves Qinghai Drought </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, March 9 (Xinhua) -- The first major snowfall on
northwest China's Qinghai Plateau since last winter has at least
to some extent relieved an extended drought.
</P>
<P>
The dry spell since last autumn has prevented Qinghai farmers
from planting crops on over 400,000 hectares of arable land. The
drought has also affected natural grassland areas covering over 16
million hectares.
</P>
<P>
The snow accumulation will not completely relieve the drought,
but will nonetheless bring life and vigor to drought-stricken
areas.
</P>
<P>
The local meteorological department reported today's snow
accumulations ranged from 0.5 mm to 2.4 mm, with more
precipitation predicted over the next few days.
</P>
<P>
Strong winds reaching as high as force 10 roared through
pastureland located at 4,000 meters above sea level in southern
part of the province on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The continuing strong winds have destroyed a number of
ramshackle houses in the area. Experts predict that southern and
western Qinghai Province, as well as areas around the Qinghai Lake,
will continue to experience windy weather over the next few days.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
