<HEADLINE> Chinese FM Spokesman on Sino-U.S. Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Zhu Bangzao told today's
press conference that the visit is another major event in Sino-U.S.
relations in the wake of the successful exchange of visits between
the heads of state of the two countries, and it will further
promote mutual understanding and expand cooperation for mutual
benefit in broad areas.
</P>
<P>
He noted that this year marks the 20th anniversary of the
establishment of Sino-U.S. diplomatic relations, and the
successful exchange of visits between the two heads of state have
pushed Sino-U.S. relations to a new stage. The bilateral relations
have maintained a good momentum in general, he added.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that remarks detrimental to Sino-U.S. relations
are "groundless, irresponsible" ,and were made "with ulterior
motives."
</P>
<P>
China and the U.S. , both influential countries in the world,
share extensive common interests, Zhu said, pointing to the fact
that both sides have been expanding cooperation in various areas,
and have conducted fruitful consultations on the issues concerning
regional and international security.
</P>
<P>
Facts prove that developing Sino-U.S. friendly relations
conforms to the fundamental interests of the two countries, and
serves peace and stability in the Asia-Pacific region and in the
world at large, he said.
</P>
<P>
Zhu reaffirmed that the Taiwan question has always been the
most important and most sensitive issue in Sino-U.S. relations.
</P>
<P>
"As long as our two sides strictly adhere to the principles of
the three China-U.S. joint communiques and the China-U.S. Joint
Statement, especially such important principles as mutual respect
for sovereignty and territorial integrity, mutual non-interference
in each other's internal affairs, equality and mutual benefit,
relations between China and the United States will enjoy a smooth
growth," he said.
</P>
<P>
China is willing to join hands with the U.S. to remove
interference and bring a healthy and steady Sino-U.S. relations
into the 21st century, he concluded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
