10.67 points to 530.53, the all-share Emas Index was up 2.53
points at 133.29, the Industrial Index gained 20.66 points to
1,001.10 and the Second Board Index rose 3.29 points to 132.36.
</P>
<P>
Gainers beat losers by 519 to 82 while 112 counters were
unchanged, 195 untraded and 15 suspended.
</P>
<P>
The day's total turnover was higher at 90.667 million shares
valued at 188.082 million ringgit (49.495 million U.S. dollars)
compared with 65.216 million shares worth 140.682 million ringgit
(37.021 million dollars) on Monday. 
</P>
