<HEADLINE> Shanghai Zoo Ships Male Panda to Chongqing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 9 (Xinhua) -- Chuanchuan, an 18-year-old panda
housed at the Shanghai Zoo, was shipped to the Chongqing Zoo for
the ninth time today to spend the March-April mating season with
Xinxing (New Star).
</P>
<P>
Chuanchuan and Xinxing have conceived seven cubs since the zoos
initiated cooperation in 1990. Three surviving cubs are growing
healthily.
</P>
<P>
Xinxing has recovered rapidly since giving birth to her last
cub in July last year, and currently eats 20-30 kg of bamboo
leaves daily, along with portions of rice flour, eggs, milk and
mincemeat.
</P>
<P>
Chuanchuan and Xinxing will be housed in separate cages until
experts confirm the beginning of the estrus period.
</P>
<P>
Experts point out that pandas are highly selective when it
comes to accepting mates, and note Chuanchuan and Xinxing have
rarely remained together throughout the entire mating season.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
