<HEADLINE> Hu Jintao Takes Part in Discussion of NPC Deputies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 9 (Xinhua) -- Hu Jintao, state vice-president
and a member of the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of
the Communist Party (CPC) of China Central Committee, called for
fostering a scientific point of view on development, opening wider
to the outside world and maintaining a high spirit.
</P>
<P>
Hu made the call at a group discussion on the government work
report attended by NPC deputies from Fujian Province.
</P>
<P>
Hu emphasized that, in the process of building a socialist
market economy, resources should be allocated and production and
goods circulation organized in accordance with supply and demand
on the market.
</P>
<P>
Since the supply and demand situation in China has undergone
great changes, he said, particular attention should be paid to the
unity of scale and structure, quantity and quality, and speed and
economic results.
</P>
<P>
Economic globalization provides China with a rare opportunity
for development but at the same time brings enormous risks, too,
he said. "We should safeguard our economic security, but this does
not mean that we should become hesitant about opening the country
wider to the outside world."
</P>
<P>
Hu noted that it is completely correct and necessary for the
country to focus on expanding domestic demand, but efforts to
develop foreign trade and introduce overseas funds should not be
slackened.
</P>
<P>
China must firmly implement the opening policy and take an
active part in international economic cooperation and competition,
he said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that keeping a high spirit is crucial for dealing
with contradictions and problems and called on cadres at all
levels to trust and rely on people in finding solutions for
problems and overcoming difficulties. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
