<HEADLINE> Microsoft's DNS to Help Asian Firms Improve Efficiency </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 9 (Xinhua) -- Microsoft Chairman Bill Gates
here today stated his vision to Asian business executives on how
his corporation can help Asian companies become efficient
enterprises for tomorrow through its Digital Nervous System (DNS).
</P>
<P>
Speaking to 160 administrative and information executives of
major Asian enterprises, who gathered here for the Asian
Enterprise Summit, Gates explained how his DNS can help them solve
business difficulties such as reducing cost, enhancing
communications and responding to market competition and
globalization of business.
</P>
<P>
During the two-day summit, leaders from 30 different industries
in Asia can have a chance to share the management experience of
big enterprises and to talk about how technology can improve their
business profits.
</P>
<P>
Nicholas Negroponte, author of best seller Being Digital, also
attended the summit. Negroponte is a professor of Media Technology
at MIT.
</P>
<P>
Delivering a keynote speech, Gates said that with the Digital
Nervous System, enterprises can make full use of the current
investment of its information infrastructure to improve their
efficiency and then become successful enterprises and establish
closer ties with their customers.
</P>
<P>
The basic elements of the high efficient DNS includes the
network function, secure E-mail, powerful data bank and other
application software.
</P>
<P>
Gates said the concept of the DNS will help enterprises
revolutionize their management methods, bring the talents of their
staff into full play and help them contact new customers and
business partners.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
