<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CPPCC Forum Opens To Views, Suggestions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 9 (Xinhua) -- Members of the Ninth National
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC) raised suggestions for maintaining social
stability at a full-member session of the committee this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan, chairman of the CPPCC National Committee, the
country's highest advisory body, and leading officials from some
central government departments attended the meeting, which serves
as a forum for CPPC National Committee members to debate issues
concerning people's livelihood, make comments and suggestions on
major state policies.
</P>
<P>
Members raised suggestions for maintaining China's social
stability, which include adopting more flexible policies for
assisting laid-off workers, making proper readjustments to the
existing wealth distribution system and developing community
services.
</P>
<P>
Some members aired views on the promotion of China's
reunification. Hu Fa-kuang, chairman of the Liberal Democratic
Federation of Hong Kong, suggested increasing cooperation between
Hong Kong and inland areas in the fields of trade, science and
technology and culture.
</P>
<P>
A member from Macao talked about broad public participation in
affairs concerning Macao's smooth transition and its smooth
return to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Members representing China Zhigong (Public Interest) Party and
the Taiwan Democratic Self-Government League (China) expounded on
favorable factors and conditions for resolving the Taiwan problem.
</P>
<P>
Other issues discussed by members include project engineering
quality and the aging of the Chinese population. 
</P>
</TEXT>
