<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Most Middle School Students Suffer Shortsightedness </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 9 (Xinhua) -- Shortsightedness arising from
excessive study and lack of care for eyes are plaguing 70 percent
of middle school students in China, according to a report in today'
s "Beijing Youth Daily".
</P>
<P>
The level of shortsightedness is serious at senior middle
schools, where students often shoulder heavier loads of study and
pay less attention to care for their eyes. A survey found about 70
percent of the students suffering shortsightedness in their last
academic year.
</P>
<P>
The survey revealed that about 22 percent of primary school
students from grade four to six were nearsighted, compared with 10
percent among younger pupils.
</P>
<P>
However, after three years' studying at junior high school,
more than half of the students had to wear glasses due to myopia,
according to the survey which was conducted by a department under
the National Bureau of Statistics.  
</P>
</TEXT>
