<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippines Senior Soccer League Draws 200 Teams </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 9 (Xinhua) -- Philippine football hits fever
pitch once again as a record field of 200 teams nationwide will
compete in the Second-P-League, the country's premier senior
soccer tournament, which is to kick off on March 21.
</P>
<P>
"The success of last year's inaugural P-League has encouraged
more teams this year to participate in the second year of our
tournament. We are expecting better and more exciting games this
year," Chris Monfort, general secretary of the organizing
Philippine Football Federation (PFF), told a meeting here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Local eliminating round has been going on throughout the
country since last December, and the regional qualifiers will
start on March 21, he added.
</P>
<P>
Top two teams from each regional tourney will advance to the
finals from May 28-June 5 in Dumaguete City, one of the country's
soccer strongholds.
</P>
<P>
Monfort said that the P-League is in line with the PFF's vision
of eventually having a full-blown professional football league in
the country, "which is the only way to really improve the sport
locally and keep us abreast with the rest of the world." 
</P>
</TEXT>
