<HEADLINE> Roma Boss Takes Legal Step to Doping Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, March 9 (Xinhua) -- Italian Serie A side AS Roma boss
Franco Sensi said Tuesday he will take legal action against soccer
officials and referees, who he believed took revenge on the pitch
to Roma coach Zdenek Zeman's doping scandal condemnation.
</P>
<P>
Enraged by Sunday's 2-1 defeat at Udinese, where Roma was
handed off with two penalties -- including a controversial hand-
ball judge in the 89th minute, Sensi said his team was punished by
referees for Zeman's prowess remark which triggered a doping
crisis in the Serie A last year.
</P>
<P>
"Roma have started legal proceedings in order to understand
what is going on and who is behind it, "Sensi said.
</P>
<P>
Sensi also denounced the work of the Italian soccer federation,
saying "the federation is dying". 
</P>
