<HEADLINE> Forest Parks Become Hot Tourist Attraction in Shaanxi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, March 9 (Xinhua) -- A green corridor linked by 16 forest
parks, on the northern slope of the Qinling Mountains, has become
a hot tourist area in northwest China's Shaanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the forests and natural reserves played
host to more than one million visitors annually in the past few
years, bringing 15 million yuan in direct income.
</P>
<P>
Urban people residing in cities on the northern slope of the
Qinling Mountains, which accounts for 80 percent of the total
number of cities in the province, make up the majority of the
tourists, according to park managers.
</P>
<P>
People like to spend their weekends and holidays in the parks,
most of which are dozens of kilometers away from their cities,
enjoying the fresh air and quietness.
</P>
<P>
Shaanxi has six state-level forest parks, four of them located
on the northern slope of the Qinling Mountains.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
