<DOCNO> XIE19990309.0151 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rainless February Recorded in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, March 9 (Xinhua) -- Data of the Macao Observatory showed
a zero precipitation record for February this year in Macao, the
first time since 1952.
</P>
<P>
The weather was fine in Macao throughout February with a few
days of overcast or mist. The temperature reached a day-time high
of 27.1 degrees Celsius, the highest for the month since 1954.
</P>
<P>
Located in the East Asia monsoon zone, Macao has an annual
average rainfall of 1,974.5 mm and the average rainfall in dry
February is 60 mm.  
</P>
</TEXT>
