<BODY>
<HEADLINE> LG to Increase Investment In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 9 (Xinhua)-- In a bid to grab a larger share of
the market, LG Electronics Inc. of the Republic of Korea is to
boost its investment in China, pushing its annual investment from
last year's 660 million US dollars to two billion US dollars by
2005.
</P>
<P>
This was announced by One S. Sung, Senior Vice President of
China Sales and Marketing at a press conference today.
</P>
<P>
Sung said that the move reflects LG's determination to make
China its most important production base.
</P>
<P>
Last year, LG Electronics (China) saw its sales revenue rise by
more than 30 percent over 1997. It sold 440 million US dollars of
products in China and exported 250 million US dollars of products
last year, he said.
</P>
<P>
Since LG Electronics Inc. entered China in 1993, it has built
ten factories, nine of which it built with Chinese partners, six
subsidiaries and six service centers. It currently employs 12,000
staff in China, with over 98 percent being Chinese.
</P>
<P>
According to a survey by the National Bureau of Statistics,
there are nearly 100 household electrical appliances producers in
China and LG's microwave ovens have the second largest share of
the market, its color TV sets are ranked thirteenth in sales
levels, its air conditioners tenth and its washing machines
seventh.  
</P>
</TEXT>
