<HEADLINE> World Cup Finals Canceled for Winds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, March 9 (Xinhua) -- Wild winds forced the cancellation
of the first day's racing at the World Cup Alpine skiing finals,
organisers announced on Tuesday in Sierra Nevada, Spain.
</P>
<P>
The men's and women's downhill races will be held on Wednesday
as originally scheduled.
</P>
<P>
According to local weather forecast, the bad weather is
expected for Thursday when the men's and women's Super-G races are
scheduled. 
</P>
</TEXT>
