<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Microsoft to Conduct Extensive Software Test in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 9 (Xinhua) -- Microsoft will conduct an
extensive test on the Chinese version of its new business software
suite, Office 2000, starting from next Monday.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest information from company sources, the
world's software giant will officially launch Office 2000 in the
third quarter of this year.
</P>
<P>
This software test will be the largest so far in China's
computer industry. A total of 21,000 copies of the test version of
the new software will be sent to professional computer engineers
through software retailers around the country.
</P>
<P>
The previous major software test in China was on Microsoft's
Windows 98 (Chinese version) last year. It involved 6,000 users.
</P>
<P>
Microsoft's Vice President in charge of desktop applications,
Jon DeVaan said Office 2000 is based on its predecessor, Office 97,
but has more integrated Internet-related information building,
release mechanisms and sharing programs.
</P>
<P>
This is in conformity with the development of computer
technologies that center on networking and the Web, said DeVaan.
</P>
<P>
According to Luo Chuan, group marketing manager of Microsoft (
China) Co., Ltd., his company will also hold preview fairs for
Office 2000 in seven major cities including Beijing, Shanghai and
Guangzhou.
</P>
<P>
"The gap between the launching of the Chinese and English
versions of Office 2000 will be 2-3 months shorter than that of
Office 97, " Luo said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese version of Office 97 came on the market in May 1997,
whereas the English version was available in January 1997.
</P>
<P>
Office 2000 will provide users with increased and improved
capacity for the Chinese language and for the first time there
will be a Chinese language grammar and spelling check.
</P>
<P>
The handwriting input of the Chinese language would involve no
other hardware than a mouse.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
