<DOCNO> XIE19990309.0160 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 1,688 Refugees from Burundi, DRC Rush to Tanzania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, March 9 (Xinhua) -- At least 1,688 new refugees
from Burundi and the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC) have
rushed to neighboring Tanzania's western region of Kigoma over the
past four days.
</P>
<P>
A main local newspaper, The Guardian, Tuesday quoted sources in
Kigoma as saying that only seven out of the 1,688 new refugees,
who were screened at the Kibirizi Reception Center for firearms,
were Burundians.
</P>
<P>
The DRC refugees were sent to the Lugufu Refugee Camp for
accommodation while their Burundian counterparts sheltered at the
Muyovosi Refugee Camp, the sources confirmed.
</P>
<P>
The refugees claimed that they were fleeing fierce fighting
between government troops and rebels in the two war-torn
countries.
</P>
<P>
No single case of cholera was recorded among the new arrivals
and their transportation went on smoothly in defiance of heavy
rains, the sources added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
