<DOCNO> XIE19990309.0161 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Swaziland to Set up Anti-Bomb Unit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, March 9 (Xinhua) -- The Swazi government is to
establish an anti-terrorist bomb unit after a blast in capital
Mbabane last year, South African Press Association reported
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The government has allocated 10 million emalangeni (1.7 million
U.S. dollars) to the royal Swaziland police to set up the unit,
the report said.
</P>
<P>
The move was aimed at preventing further bomb attacks like the
one last November, in which part of the deputy prime minister's
office building in the center of Mbabane was destroyed and a
security guard was killed.
</P>
<P>
The funds will provide for the training of officers in
bomb-related matters, including bomb disposal and detection, and
for the purchase of equipment, such as X-ray machines. It will
also provide for the training of sniffer dogs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
