<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Project Launched to Promote Renewable Energy Technologies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 9 (Xinhua)-- A new project to promote the
commercialization of renewable energy technologies in China has
recently been launched jointly by the Chinese Government and the
United Nations Development Program.
</P>
<P>
The five-year project involves an investment of more than 25
million US dollars, among which over 11 million US dollars will be
input by China.
</P>
<P>
The project is aimed at supporting government initiatives to
lessen the dependence on fossil fuels and strengthen the country's
capacity to promote renewable energy. It is also expected to
remove a range of financial, economic, information and technical
barriers to increase the market penetration of the energy
technologies.
</P>
<P>
Project activities include supporting the formation of a
renewable energy industries association in China, international
training for policy makers and professionals, development of
standards, and technology demonstrations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
