<DOCNO> XIE19990309.0172 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Industry Grows Rapidly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 9 (Xinhua)-- China's total industrial value-
added output increased by 10.6 percent in the past two months on a
year-on-year basis to reach 280 billion yuan (33.7 billion US
dollars), according to a report released today by the National
Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the sales-to-production ratio was raised by 0.29
percentage points to 93.62 percent in the same period.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that state-owned firms completed 160.7 billion
yuan of industrial incremental output in the January-February
period, up 8.8 percent over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
As the state increased investment in infrastructure, heavy
industry registered a rapid growth rate of 11.7 percent, 2.2
percentage points faster than that of light industry. The country
generated 179.2 billion kwh of electricity, up six percent over
last year's same period.
</P>
<P>
The first two months also witnessed a sharp increase in
agricultural means of production output. Statistics show that
chemical fertilizer output increased by 16.1 percent while that of
chemical pesticides was up by 17.3 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
