<HEADLINE> Thai Bourse Down 7.09 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, March 9 (Xinhua) -- The Stock Exchange of Thailand
(SET) index on Tuesday lost 7.09 points from Monday to close at
329.59.
</P>
<P>
Some 207 million shares worth 2.16 billion baht (58.6 million
U.S. dollars) changed hands Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The SET index Monday gained 0.47 points from last Friday to
close at 336.68. 
</P>
</TEXT>
