<HEADLINE> Chinese Foreign Minister to Visit Five European Countries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 9 (Xinhua) -- At the invitation of Foreign
Minister Tarja Halonen of Finland, Foreign Minister Anna Lindh of
Sweden, Foreign Minister Knut Vollebaek of Norway, Foreign
Minister Niels Helveg Petersen of Denmark and Foreign Minister
Joschka Fischer of Germany, Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan
will pay official visits to the above five countries starting from
March 17, 1999.
</P>
<P>
This was announced by Foreign Ministry spokesman Zhu Bangzao at
the regular press conference this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Tang will also attend the second Asia-Europe Meeting (ASEM)
Foreign Ministers' Meeting to be held in Berlin, Germany, from
March 28 to 29 and will hold consultations with the foreign
ministers of the European Union Troika, Zhu said. 
</P>
