<HEADLINE> Chinese FM Spokesman on Khmer Rouge Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 9 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Ministry Spokesman
Zhu Bangzao said today that it is up to the Cambodian government
and people to decide independently the matter of how to deal with
former Khmer Rouge leaders, as it is completely their internal
affair.
</P>
<P>
 The Khmer Rouge issue has become "historical", Zhu told a
regular press conference here this afternoon when asked to comment
on the handling of Khmer Rouge leaders.
</P>
<P>
 China appreciates the policy outlined recently by the new
Cambodian government, which aims at safeguarding the country's
stability and revitalizing the economy, Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
 He went on to say that the current urgent task for Cambodia
is to consolidate the progress made in national reconciliation and
concentrate on economic construction, which serves the fundamental
interest of the Cambodian people as well as peace and stability in
the region.
</P>
<P>
The international community should respect the choice of the
Cambodian government and people and engage more in what benefits
peace, stability and national reconciliation, the spokesman said.
</P>
