<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, March 9 (Xinhua) -- Polish President Aleksander
Kwasniewski is due to pay a two-day official visit to Sri Lanka to
further improve bilateral trade relations, a press release said
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Kwasniewski will come here on Saturday, March 13, at the
invitation of Sri Lankan President Chandrika Kumaratunga in return
to her visit to Poland early this year, said the Government
Information Department in the release.
</P>
<P>
He will be accompanied by a 75-member trade delegation from
Poland, said the release.
</P>
<P>
The delegation is expected to enter into a memorandum of
understanding with the Ceylon Chamber of Commerce, with regard to
trade relations between the two countries. The move is likely to
favor Sri Lanka's tea export sector greatly, it added. 
