<BODY>
<HEADLINE> "Independence of Tibet": Outcome of Foreign Aggression (18) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
So we can draw the following conclusions by reviewing the
history of imperialist aggression of Tibet and the evolution of
activities aimed at "Independence of Tibet".
</P>
<P>
First, Tibet has always been under the sovereign rule of China,
since it came under the rule of the central government of the Yuan
Dynasty in the 13th Century. However, there had been no mention of
"Tibetan Independence" or the problem of "Tibetan Independence "
until the beginning of the 20th century. The "Independence of
Tibet" became a problem in the early period of the current century,
when The British government attempted to separate Tibet from the
motherland and to turn Tibet into one of its dependencies, by
encouraging the pro-British activists among the upper classes of
Tibetan society to split from China in the name of "Independence
of Tibet". Historical facts have showed that the "Independence of
Tibet" is an outcome of the aggression of imperialists and their
attempt to split China. Following that, the international anti-
China forces continued to play the card of "Independence of Tibet"
in both the Cold War period and the late 1980s, attempting to
split Tibet from Chinese territory.
</P>
<P>
Second, the international anti-China forces have deployed a
large number of human resources, materials and funds to aid the
activities of "Independence of Tibet" over the past century, ever
since the British government plotted to separate Tibet from China
at the Simrall Conference held in 1913. But all their attempts
have ended in failure, due to strong opposition from and struggles
by all nationalities of Chinese people, including all the Tibetan
people and Buddhists. All the nationalities of Chinese people have
helped and supported each other over a long period of history to
protect the motherland and fight against foreign invaders. They
have thus cultivated a deep and long lasting brotherhood and an
unbroken cohesion that will never separate them from each other.
This is one of the most important reasons why all the attempts by
both imperialists and a small number of separatists among the
upper echelons of Tibetan society in spitting Tibet from China
were unfruitful.
</P>
<P>
Third, at present, China has witnessed a rapid economic growth
rate over the past few years, with people's living standards
consistently improving, and comprehensive national power and
national defense strength greatly being upgraded. All Chinese
people, under the guidance of the Deng Xiaoping theory of building
socialism with Chinese characteristics, are continuing to
implement the policies of reform and opening-up. Tibet has also
made remarkable achievements in economic progress, and witnessed
social stability since the quelling of rebellion in 1959,
particularly over the past two decades of reform and opening-up.
The Tibetan people are living and working in peace and contentment,
as their living standards continue to improve. They now are eager
for peace and development, and those separatists will find less
and less support among the Tibetan people. So any attempts or
plots to split Tibet from China in the disguise of "Independence
of Tibet" staged either by the international anti-China forces or
Dalai Lama group are doomed to failure.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
