<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Return to Motherland Brings New Opportunities for Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 9 (Xinhua) -- A Macao member of the Ninth
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC), China's top advisory body, said here today
that the return of Macao to its motherland at the end of this year
has brought new opportunities for the region's economic and social
development.
</P>
<P>
"With continuous supply of production and living materials from
the interior areas and the backing of a huge domestic market,
Macao can further promote its economic and trade relations with
the interior areas and create broad room for local economic
development," said Vitor Ng, president of the Macao Association
for Exports and Imports, at a speech meeting of the ongoing Second
Session of the Ninth CPPCC National Committee this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Ng noted that according to a work plan of the Preparatory
Committee for the Macao Special Administrative Region (SAR) of the
National People's Congress, China's legislature, a Selection
Committee will be established in Macao in early April for the
election of the first Chief Executive of the SAR in mid or late
May.
</P>
<P>
"We believe that the Preparatory Committee will choose members
of the Selection Committee in an open, fair, democratic and honest
manner," said Ng. "We also have confidence that the first Chief
Executive elected by the Selection Committee will be a highly-
competent leader with personal integrity."
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that at present, a major concern for all
people in Macao is to prompt the Portuguese side to step up
efforts for the early resolution of problems relating to a smooth
transfer of power, so as to ensure Macao's smooth transition.
</P>
<P>
"Though new progress has been achieved on several major issues,
such as localization of Macao's civil servants and of local laws
and the official status of the Chinese language, greater efforts
are needed to ensure the smooth transition of Macao," he said.
</P>
<P>
Macao people sincerely hope that the Portuguese side will
continue to cooperate with the Chinese side in a candid and
friendly manner, and promote satisfactory resolution of all issues
relating to the transfer of power and a smooth transition with a
pragmatic and responsible attitude, he added.
</P>
<P>
He finally called on all Macao residents to actively
participate in and give full support to the preparatory work for
the establishment of the SAR government, and make every effort for
a smooth implementation of the "one country, two systems"
principle in Macao and for the maintenance of Macao's economic
prosperity and social stability. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
