<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Draft Amendments to Constitution Submitted to NPC Deliberation (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 9 (Xinhua) -- The Standing Committee of the
National People's Congress (NPC) today submitted draft amendments
to the Constitution to the current Second Session of the Ninth NPC
for examination.
</P>
<P>
The draft proposes to add "Deng Xiaoping Theory" and "governing
the country according to law and building a socialist country
governed according to law" into the Constitution.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the draft proposes to change the status and
function of the non-public sector such as self-employed and
private businesses in China's economy from being "a complement to
the socialist public economy" to "an important component of the
socialist market economy".
</P>
<P>
Tian Jiyun, a vice-chairman of the NPC Standing Committee, made
explanations to the draft amendments at today's meeting, which was
attended by 2,781 NPC deputies.
</P>
<P>
He said that the present Constitution adopted in 1982 is a good
one and has played an important role in the country's political,
economic and social life, and it was revised twice in 1988 and
1993 with the constant development of China's reforms, opening up.
</P>
<P>
The principle for amendments is that "we will only make
amendments that are deemed necessary and relevant conditions are
ripe," Tian said.
</P>
<P>
Based on the report of the 15th National Congress of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) and a wide-ranging collection of
the opinions and suggestions among people from all walks of life,
the CPC Central Committee put forward a proposal on revising part
of the Constitution to the NPC Standing Committee on January 22
this year, according to sources of the NPC.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990309.0187 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Draft Method for Electing Macao Deputies Submitted for NPC Deliberation (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 9 (Xinhua) -- The Macao Special Administrative
Region (SAR), to be founded after China resumes the exercise of
sovereignty over Macao at the end of this year, will have 12
deputies to the Ninth National People's Congress (NPC), China's
legislature.
</P>
<P>
This is the stipulation of a draft method for electing Macao
SAR deputies to the Ninth NPC, which was submitted to the ongoing
Second Session of the Ninth NPC for deliberation this morning.
</P>
<P>
The Ninth NPC now already has five Macao deputies, who were
elected to the top legislature by the Provincial People's Congress
of Guangdong. The draft method says that the five will
automatically become Macao SAR deputies after the founding of the
SAR.
</P>
<P>
The other seven deputies should be elected by an election
conference established in the Macao SAR, says the draft.
</P>
<P>
While explaining the draft to the NPC session, He Chunlin,
secretary-general of the NPC Standing Committee and an executive
member of the session Presidium, said that according to a method
for electing NPC deputies in various provinces, autonomous regions
and municipalities in the interior areas, one NPC deputy should be
elected from about every 220,000 urban residents and from about
every 880,000 rural residents.
</P>
<P>
According to 1997 statistics Macao only had a population of 450,
000 people. However, to enable Macao deputies to form an
independent delegation to the NPC, the draft stipulates that the
number of Macao SAR NPC deputies should be 12, He explained. (
more)
nnnn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990309.0188 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Draft Method for Electing Macao Deputies Submitted for NPC Deliberation (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The draft also stipulates that the election conference in the
Macao SAR should comprise Chinese citizens from the Selection
Committee for the first Macao SAR government, NPC deputies in the
Macao region who have not entered the Selection Committee, members
of the Ninth National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC) who are residents of the Macao SAR
but are not concurrently members of the Selection Committee, and
members of the Macao SAR Legislative Council who are Chinese
citizens.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that the Selection Committee for the first
Macao SAR government has a broad representation, with members from
all circles of life and all social sectors in Macao.
</P>
<P>
"Therefore, it is appropriate to form the election conference
mainly with Chinese citizens from the Selection Committee," he
noted.
</P>
<P>
The election procedure stipulated by the draft method is: the
first meeting of the election conference will be called by the NPC
Standing Committee, and the meeting will select nine conference
members to form a presidium, which will preside over the election
conference.
</P>
<P>
More than 10 members of the election conference can jointly
nominate candidates for the position of an NPC deputy, and
differential voting by secret ballot will be adopted, says the
draft.
</P>
<P>
It adds that the election result will be announced by the
presidium and be reported to the Subcommittee for Examining
Deputies' Qualifications under the NPC Standing Committee.
</P>
<P>
The draft, which also makes stipulations on issues like
possible resignation of elected deputies and by-elections for the
deputies, has been initially examined at the Seventh Meeting of
the Ninth NPC Standing Committee before being submitted to the
current NPC full session, He said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990309.0189 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Draft Amendments to Constitution Submitted to NPC Deliberation (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The NPC Standing Committee discussed the proposal by the CPC
Central Committee and tabled the draft amendments to the
Constitution to the NPC session for examination according to law,
the sources said..
</P>
<P>
The draft includes six amendments to the Constitution,
according to the vice chairman of the NPC Standing Committee.
</P>
<P>
The first is to add "Deng Xiaoping Theory" into the
Constitution and is, accordingly, to change "in line with the
theory of building socialism with Chinese characteristics" to "
along the road of building socialism with Chinese characteristics",
and "China is currently in the primary stage of socialism" will be
revised into "will be over a long period of time in the primary
stage of socialism". The content of "develop a socialist market
economy" will be added into the Constitution, according to Tian.
</P>
<P>
Tian said the amendment shows the guiding role of Deng Xiaoping
Theory in China's socialist modernization drive and reflects the
consensus and the will of the Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
Deng Xiaoping Theory is the succession and development of Mao
Zedong Thought, a guiding theory for the Chinese people to realize
the socialist modernization through reforms and opening up, and a
new stage of the development of Marxism in China, he said.
</P>
<P>
Tian stressed that China must hold high the great banner of
Deng Xiaoping Theory and use Deng's theory to guide the work in
all fields in the process of reforms, opening up and the
modernization drive, and this is an unshakable conclusion drawn by
the Chinese people of all nationalities from the history and
reality.
</P>
<P>
He said: "To enshrine Deng Xiaoping Theory in the Constitution
is of great immediate and far-reaching historic significance to
the victorious advance of building the cause of socialism with
Chinese characteristics."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990309.0190 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Draft Amendments to Constitution Submitted to NPC Deliberation (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Explaining the addition of governing the country according to
law into the Constitution, Tian said that to govern the country
according to the law is a basic principle for the ruling CPC in
running the country and an important guarantee for the country's
long tranquillity.
</P>
<P>
"Enshrining 'governing the country according to law and
building a socialist country governed according to law' is of
great significance to adhering the basic principle of governing
the country according to law, to constantly improving the
socialist legal system, to developing socialist democratic
politics, and promoting the economic restructuring and
construction," Tian said.
</P>
<P>
The draft suggests to add into the Constitution: "In the
primary stage of socialism, the state upholds the basic economic
system in which the public ownership is dominant and diverse forms
of ownership develop side by side, and upholds the distribution
system with distribution according to work remaining dominant and
a variety of modes of distribution coexisting."
</P>
<P>
Tian explained that the clear definition on the basic economic
and distribution systems in the primary stage of socialism in the
Constitution is conducive to uphold and improve the above-
mentioned systems and further emancipate and develop productive
forces in the reforms, opening up and socialist modernization
drive.
</P>
<P>
According to the guidelines of the 15th CPC National Congress,
the draft adds the stipulation: "The rural collective economic
organizations follow the two-tier operations system that combines
unified and separate operations on the basis of the household
contract operations," and accordingly, abolishes the wording "the
responsibility system mainly based on household contract that
links remuneration to output" in the existing Constitution.
</P>
<P>
Tian said that the two-tier operation system that combines
unified and separate operations is a operation system that
combines the unified collective operations with household contract
operations within the rural collective economic organizations, and
the household contract operations constitute the basis of the two-
tier operation system, he explained.
</P>
<P>
Tian added that enshrining the two-tier operation system into
the Constitution is conducive to ensuring the system to stay long
and unchanged and to be constantly improved and to ensuring the
healthy development of the collective economy in rural areas. (
more)

nnnn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990309.0191 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Draft Amendments to Constitution Submitted to NPC Deliberation (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Regarding the status and role of the non-public economy, the
draft proposes to add into the Constitution: "Non-public sector
comprising self-employed and private businesses within the domain
stipulated by law is an important component of the country's
socialist market economy," and, accordingly, abolish the wording
that the self-employed and private businesses are "a complement to
the socialist public economy" in the current Constitution.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the draft suggests to change other wording of the
same article to "The state protects the legitimate rights and
interests of the self-employed and private businesses, and
exercises guidance, supervision and management over them."
</P>
<P>
Thus, Tian said, the status and role of the non-public economy
in China's socialist market economy are further clearly defined
and this is conducive to its healthy development, Tian explained.
</P>
<P>
The draft suggests to revise the wording of "counter-
revolutionary activities" in Article 28 into "crimes jeopardizing
the state security".
</P>
<P>
Tian said that in 1997's revision of the Criminal Law, "counter-
revolutionary crimes" was revised to "crimes of jeopardizing state
security", and therefore, it is completely necessary to revise the
wording of "counter-revolutionary activities" in the Constitution.
</P>
</TEXT>
