<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Somalia Accuses Ethiopian Forces of Invasion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, March 9 (Xinhua) -- A massive looting operation of
private properties by Ethiopian forces has been reported in the
Somali border town of Balanballe controlled by the Somali National
Front (SNF) faction of Marehan clan.
</P>
<P>
Reports from the central region of Galgudud indicated that
hundreds of heavily armed infantry Ethiopians crossed into
Balanballe Sunday night. They were supported by about a dozen of
armed personnel carriers and had entered into the town a little
after midnight. The Ethiopian soldiers did not fire a single shot
during their alleged "invasion", but had immediately started
searching houses, chemists and food stores.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian soldiers have taken away two VHF radios, quite a
few guns, car-batteries and all of the medicine in the only
chemist shop of the town.
</P>
<P>
One of the elders of the town who preferred to be anonymous
contacted reporters in Mogadishu through the VHF radio, said the
officials of the invading Ethiopian troops admitted they were
merely after what they called the fundamentalists group of
Al-Itihad Al-Islam whom they fought in Gedo region, southern
Somalia, two years ago.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopians said they had some traces of Al-Itihad men in the
town which is the sole motive of their crossing-over, a usual
pretext of the Ethiopian invasions into Somalia which lacks a
central government since 1991.
</P>
<P>
The elder said the Ethiopian forces, many of whom had retreated
back to their barracks across the border Monday evening, did not
kill anyone, but took a man with them while two other men are
still missing. The man they took is called Mohamed Fayoko Ali
Dharar who was very well known in the town for his seriousness,
but not very much of a religious figure.
</P>
<P>
Independent sources said some well known businessmen and
religious scholars have already fled the town before dawn Tuesday
morning, before the Ethiopians would again start killing or
arresting any man growing beards. Growing beards by men is
recommended by Islam according to the narration from Prophet
Mohamed.
</P>
<P>
Jama Howleh, the SNFspokesman here in Mogadishu, also confirmed
the invasion and condemned the act which he characterized as
provocative. He said the Ethiopians still remain in full
deployment of their forces along the border with Somalia, while
controlling the two towns of Bulo Hawo and Dolow-Somalia of Gedo
region, an act which is contrary to the international regulations
regarding the territorial integrity of a nation and its
sovereignty. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
