<HEADLINE> "Independence of Tibet": Outcome of Foreign Aggression (15) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The United States terminated its financial, arms and other
material aid to the separatists aiming at the independence of
Tibet after Nixon's visit to China in 1972 and the establishment
of the China-U.S. diplomatic relations in 1976.
</P>
<P>
As China's international status rose and the U.S. tried to
readjust its relations with China in an effort to achieve world
hegemony against the Soviet Union, support from major western
countries to the Tibetan separatists was contained to a large
extent from mid 1970s through early 1980s.
</P>
<P>
III. "Independence of Tibet" is a card in the hands of anti-
China international forces to separate China
</P>
<P>
After the ending of the Cold War period, the involvement of the
international forces in the independence of Tibet movement entered
into the third stage.
</P>
<P>
Since the mid 1980s, a group of younger generation of
separatists of the "Tibetan Youth Conference" have taken major
positions in the "government in exile." the western educated
separtatists have made attempts to seek foreign support,
internationalize the Tibetan issue and stir up riots in Tibet.
</P>
<P>
The Dalai group held a high-level meeting in April 1987, and
drew up lesson from its previous unsuccessul "independence of
Tibet" activities. They also set up plans to organize
demonstrations and riots in Lhasa and other places.
</P>
<P>
The Dalai group has also sent its members in the name of
various organizations to lobby foreign government leaders,
parlament members and officials of non-government insitutions for
the independence of Tibet.
</P>
<P>
These people have distorted history, denied the sovereignty of
the China's central government over Tibet, and claimed that Tibet
was an independent country. They have also attacked the Chinese
central government over its policies of Tibet under the disguise
of the human rights.
</P>
<P>
The international anti-China forces regarded the independence
of Tibet activities as an excellent card in their accusation of
China and have renewed their opposition against China using "
independence of Tibet" as a breakthrough.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
