<HEADLINE> Prolonged Drought In Southwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
CHENGDU, March 9 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Sichuan Province
has been suffering from a prolonged drought since last October
that has affected 6.5 million people, 16 million head of livestock,
and 906,700 hectares of crops.
</P>
<P>
Two counties near the city of Nanchong in eastern Sichuan have
been the most seriously affected. The city of Wanyuan got only 50
mm of rainfall in the past 4 months, about 60 percent below normal.
Local people have to carry drinking water from miles away.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has sent work groups to drought-
affected areas and allocated special materials and funds for them.
</P>
</TEXT>
