<HEADLINE> FM Spokesman on Taiwan's TMD Attempt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 9 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman
Zhu Bangzao reiterated here today that China firmly opposed the
attempt to include Taiwan in the Theater Missile Defense (TMD)
system developed by the United States and Japan.
</P>
<P>
Answering a question at a press conference, Zhu said that the
so-called claim that China deployed missiles along the southeast
coast aimed at Taiwan is the excuse some sides used when they
sought to proliferate or introduce TMD into Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
The effort to incorporate Taiwan into TMD demonstrated the
ulterior motive of some people to obstruct the great cause of
China's reunification, he said.
</P>
<P>
Some people inside the Taiwan authorities are also speeding up
their efforts to squeeze into the TMD system, Zhu said, adding
that such activities are aimed at seeking protection from foreign
forces, stalling the reunification and splitting the motherland.
</P>
<P>
"All these attempts are what we firmly oppose," he added.
</P>
