<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Turkish Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, March 9 (Xinhua) -- The following are the major news
items in leading Turkish newspapers on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Hurriyet (Freedom):
</P>
<P>
-- Turkish gendarme forces killed five rebels of the Turkish
Workers and Peasants Liberation Army (TIKKO) in an armed clash at
Coregibuyuk village in Tokat province near northern Black Sea late
Monday night.
</P>
<P>
The TIKKO has claimed responsibility for the attempt to murder
Cankiri Governor Ayhan Cevik, who was injured in a bomb blast
Friday morning when his car was passing through the Republic
district of Cankiri city.
</P>
<P>
Daily News:
</P>
<P>
-- Turkish Parliament Speaker Hikmet Cetin called on the
legislature to hold an extraordinary session Saturday to debate on
whether to hold the local and parliamentary elections at the same
day.
</P>
<P>
A total of 116 disgruntled deputies said that they have
signed a petition sent to the speaker because they believe that
holding two elections together will harm Turkey.
</P>
<P>
Milliyet (National):
</P>
<P>
-- Turkey's highest court, Constitutional Court, rejected an
appeal lodged by Court of Appeals chief Prosecutor Vural Savas,
which demanded the closure of a Kurdish party and ban its
participation in the upcoming April 18 elections.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued by the court ruled the People's Democracy
Party, which is allegedly linked to the outlawed Kurdish Workers'
Party, can run in the local and parliamentary elections.
</P>
