<HEADLINE> Manila Mulls Over Legal Action Against Australian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 9 (Xinhua) -- President Joseph Estrada said
Tuesday that his government is considering legal action against an
Australian investigator for taking the government on a wild goose
chase after the alleged ill-gotten wealth of the late President
Ferdinand Marcos.
</P>
<P>
In an interview here, Estrada said he has instructed Magdangal
Elma, chairman of the Presidential Commission on Good Government
(PCGG), to study what actions to take against Reiner Jacobi.
</P>
