to recover the amount.
</P>
<P>
But Estrada said a discussion Monday night with Elma showed
that Jacobi's claim had no factual basis.
</P>
<P>
"There is no evidence, it's all a bum steer. It merely muddled
up efforts to recover the Marcos wealth because it raised false
hopes among the people," Estrada said.
</P>
<P>
In a radio interview Tuesday morning, Executive Secretary
Ronaldo Zamora said the government is eyeing the prosecution of
Jacobi, especially if he continues with his "fantastic" claims.
</P>
<P>
Jacobi should be charged for his attempts to take the
government for a ride, Zamora said.
</P>
<P>
Zamora also said Jacobi was the one who led the government on
an earlier wild goose chase when he claimed there was a 3,000-ton
gold hoard belonging to the Marcoses near the Kloten Airport in
Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
Government teams and representatives from the Swiss government
rushed to the site but found nothing, he said. 
