<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990309.0239 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> "Independence of Tibet": Outcome of Foreign Aggression (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Revolution of 1911 founded the Republic of China. Britain
took advantage of chaos in China's domestic political situation
during this period when the country had no time to attend to the
matters in Tibet, and made a set of new policies in order to
control Tibet and split it from China.
</P>
<P>
The new policies mainly included firstly changing the political
status of Tibet, namely, to separate Tibet from China and,
secondly annexing a large territory in the southeastern region of
Tibet bordering India.
</P>
<P>
The Memorandum Respecting the Situation in the Countries
bordering on India's North-Eastern Frontier of the India Office of
the British government altered China's sovereignty over Tibet into
a suzerainty.
</P>
<P>
The memorandum specified clearly that Tibet retained in name
its autonomy under China's suzerainty, but in fact was dependent
on the government of India absolutely. And an organization
repelling both China and Russia must be instituted.
</P>
<P>
That attempt to totally reject the jurisdiction of China's
sovereignty over Tibet, put Tibet under the complete control of
Britain and changed Tibet into a dependency of Britain.
</P>
<P>
The document further explained that the status of Tibet should
be equivalent to that of Nepal and Bhutan. The two countries were
turned into dependencies of Britain after several large-scale
wars of aggression Britain had waged against them and the signing
of unequal treaties it subsequently signed with them at that time.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990309.0240 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> "Independence of Tibet": Outcome of Foreign Aggression (5) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The document expounded British strategy without any reservation
that Tibet still needed the fabrication of so-called China's
suzerainty then. But it should be under the control of Britain
completely, and then changed into Britain's protectorate by this
means. In effect it was only a change of name.
</P>
<P>
It is quite clear that within Britain's policies, Tibet is in
fact Britain's protectorate even though it remains under China's
suzerainty in name, or it has implemented so-called autonomy, or
proposed for independence.
</P>
<P>
The document also set forth a series of measures to realize
this goal, such as to instigate pro-Britain elements including
Dasang Zhamdui to return to Tibet and establish a pro-British
government.
</P>
<P>
The measures included holding talks with Russia to revise the
agreement on Tibet signed in 1907, in order to remove the hurdle
of Britain's control over Tibet and split it from China.
</P>
<P>
Since Britain had recognized Tibet as a part of China in its
former treaties signed with the Chinese government, Britain made
desperate efforts to abrogate the former treaties and conclude new
ones asking China to abandon the sovereignty over Tibet.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
