<BODY>
<HEADLINE> "Independence of Tibet": Outcome of Foreign Aggression (8) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After the failure of the Simla Conference,the Britain continued
its diplomatic and material support for the pro-British upper-
class forces in Tibet. It carried out various kinds of tricks in
an attempt to realize its ambition.
</P>
<P>
First, the British government offered large amounts of weapons
and ammunition to the Tibetan local government and urged the
Tibetan army to invade parts of Sichuan and Qinghai, in a bid to
realize by force the dream of a "Greater Tibet", which it failed
to achieve at the Simla conference table.
</P>
<P>
Secondly, Bell, a British official, visited Tibet again in 1920
to incite Tibet against the central Government and cut the
importance of the central government's order of sending generals
Li Zhonglian and Zhu Xiu to Tibet to restore its political links
with the central government. Taking advantage of the 13th Dalai
Lama's implementation of new policies, Bell persuaded him to
expand the Tibetan army and widely collect funds for the army, in
a bid to make preparations for another eastward invasion and the
establishment of a "Greater Tibet".
</P>
<P>
Thirdly, Bell assisted a senior Tibetan army officer to
establish a secret organization which planned a coup against the
13th Dalai Lama to deprive the Dalai lama's secular and cabinet
ministers of power in 1924, in an effort to speed up Britain's
complete control of Tibet.
</P>
<P>
However, the plot was unveiled before its operation and the
British ploy suffered a heavy setback.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990309.0244 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ugandan Mayor May Return from U.S. in November: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, March 9 (Xinhua) -- Mayor of Uganda's capital city
Kampala, Nasser Sebaggala, who was sentenced to 15 months'
imprisonment for financial fraud in the United States on February
24, will complete his term and return home to perform his mayoral
duties in November this year.
</P>
<P>
Paul Kelly, lawyer of the embattled mayor, made these remarks
when interviewed by the New Vision paper Monday.
</P>
<P>
He said Sebaggala will benefit from the "good time" policy
under which his jail term will be reduced by five months.
</P>
<P>
A 15-month sentence in the U.S. means serving about 12 months.
 Sebaggala will also get credit for the time he has already served
in prison, which means he will be freed in less than nine months,
the lawyer was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the mayor is entitled to the deduction of three
months from the jail term because he has and will always behave
well while in jail.
</P>
<P>
Sebaggala's political assistant Matthias Nsubuga also said the
mayor will return to take on his duties as the Mayor of Kampala.
</P>
<P>
In Kampala, there has been a loud outcry for Sebaggala's
stepping down and authorities here said they are studying the
mayor's case and will come up with a solution very soon.
</P>
<P>
Sebaggala was sentenced in February and ordered to pay a
10,000-U.S. dollars fine and to refund 44,000 dollars he
fraudulently withdrew from Bank Boston.
</P>
<P>
The court also ordered him to pay immediately 800 dollars'
assessment fee. Sebaggala's sentence runs from December 4 when he
was convicted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
