<HEADLINE> Qatar Airways Rated Among Best Airlines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, March 9 (Xinhua) -- Qatar Airways has been rated
among the top three of its kind in view of the economic class
service offered by a selection of international airlines, the Gulf
News daily of the United Arab Emirates (UAE) reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In a survey conducted recently by British Business Traveler
magazine, Qatar Airways' daily Doha-London flight, an Airbus
A300-60R, got high marks in five categories of service, including
check-in, boarding, seat comfort, the flight and arrival.
</P>
<P>
Qatar Airways "spared no effort" in offering good service and
its service was "efficient and friendly, despite the frequent
demands made by passengers," the survey said.
</P>
<P>
The highly personalized service provided by the Qatar Airways
cabin crew received a special mention: " ... the friendly,
courteous cabin crew were at pains to help everyone as much as
they could."
</P>
<P>
Chief Executive Officer of Qatar Airways Akbar Al Baker said
after receiving the result of the survey that "as this survey
placed us against some of the biggest airlines in the world, we
are delighted with the outcome."
</P>
<P>
"The fact that it focuses on the economy class service
highlights our commitment to providing all of our passengers with
an equally high level of service across all sectors," he added.
</P>
