<HEADLINE> Private Sector Emerges as Economic Growth Point of Yunnan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, March 9 (Xinhua) -- The private sector has emerged as
a new growth point of the economy of Yunnan Province, southwest
China, with the total output value in 1998 reaching 11.65 billion
yuan (1.4 billion US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The 1998 output value for the individual and private economies
in Yunnan accounted for 45 percent of its gross domestic product.
</P>
<P>
The province has introduced a number of policies and
regulations designed to encourage and protect development of the
individual and private economies.
</P>
<P>
Local governments at all levels have formed special groups to
help solve problems to promote the growth of the private sector.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show the province had over 774,600 private
businesses and companies at the end of 1998, up 16.2 percent on
the previous year. The private sector employed 1.54 million people
and had amassed registered capital of some 18.6 billion yuan at
the end of 1998.
</P>
<P>
The private sector also gave strong support to the reform of
state enterprises in 1998, by providing jobs for 404,000 people,
including a large number of laid-off workers from state
enterprises. 
</P>
</TEXT>
