<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-09 08:11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jordanian Teenager Arrested for Alleged Honor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, March 9 (Xinhua) -- A 17-year-old Jordanian was
arrested for shooting at his pregnant sister to cleanse his honor
Sunday night, the semiofficial Jordan Times reported on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The young man, who turned himself in to police, claimed he
wanted to kill his sister to cleanse his honor because his elder
sister was found pregnant out of wedlock.
</P>
<P>
The gunshot has inflicted wounds to the chest, neck and upper
limbs of the 19-year-old young woman.
</P>
<P>
This is the latest case of the so-called "honor killing" in the
desert kingdom, where some women are either killed or critically
injured each year for alleged fornication or immoral behavior with
men other than their husbands.
</P>
<P>
The "executors" are often their husbands or brothers, who
seldom face heavy sentences if they could provide evidence or
argument for such killing. And the Jordanian society also tends to
sympathize with men convicted of the action.
</P>
<P>
However, human rights campaigners in the kingdom have clamored
for amendments to the laws for tougher punishment on honor
killers, but the calls largely fell on deaf ears. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
