<HEADLINE>   Duncan Named NBA Player of the Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 8 (Xinhua) -- San Antonio Spurs forward Tim
Duncan, who averaged 27.5 points in four victories, today was
named NBA player of the Week for the period ending Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Spur's leading score, Duncan led San Antonio to a 4-0
record, including three road wins. He also averaged 11.5 rebounds
and 3.25 blocks while shooting 52.4 percent from the field.
</P>
<P>
Duncan raised his season average nearly two points to 20.8 per
game. He closed out the week with 34 points, 13 rebounds, three
blocks and three steals in Sunday's 106-96 victory at Denver.
Duncan is 12th in the league in scoring and third in rebounding,
averaging 12.3 per contest.
</P>
