<HEADLINE> Moderate Quake Hits Southwestern Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, March 9 (Xinhua) -- A moderate earthquake measuring 4.6
on the open-ended Richter scale jolted Kumamoto Prefecture and
nearby prefectures in southwestern Japan on Tuesday, the
Meteorological Agency said.
</P>
<P>
There were no immediate reports of casualties or damage from
the quake.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter of the quake, which occurred at 12:53 p.m. (local
time), was estimated to be in the Aso area in Kumamoto Prefecture,
the agency said. 
