<HEADLINE> Xinhua World Economic Summary at 0500 GMT, March 9 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON -- Britain's opposition Conservative Party Monday opened
a new phase of its battle to prevent Britain from joining Europe's
single currency on Monday by setting up a commission to examine
the benefits of keeping sterling.
</P>
<P>
Conservative leader William Hague told a news conference the
commission, under former trade secretary Sir John Nott, would look
at how Britain could prosper if it chose to retain the pound.
</P>
<P>
Hague has ruled out Conservative support for Britain adopting
the euro in the current parliament or the next, which could mean
as late as 2007, according to local median reports.(UK-Euro Anti-
Campaign)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NEW YORK -- Dow Jones industrial average moved own slightly
Monday after last week's strong rally.
</P>
<P>
At the close of trading, the dow fell 8.47 to 9,727.61. Last
Friday, the blue chip index shot up 268.68 points at a record high
of 9,736.08, smashing the previous high of 9,643.32 set on January
8. (US-Wall Street-Closing)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MANILA -- Urging the banking system to follow its lead, The
Central Bank of Philippines (BSP) reduced its key interest rates
and other term rates Monday.
</P>
<P>
The BSP's overnight lending and borrowing rates were reduced by
25 basis points to 14.25 percent and 12.25 percent respectively.
(Philippines-Interest Rates)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
VIENNA -- The average OPEC oil basket price rose to 10.44 U.S.
dollars per barrel last week from 10.17 dollars in the previous
week, as showed by statistics released here Monday by the
Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC).
</P>
<P>
The average OPEC oil price in February stood at 10.02 dollars
per barrel, down 0.72 dollars compared with 10.74 dollars in
January, and also lower than the average price of 12.28 dollars
last year and 18.68 dollars in 1997 as well as the OPEC reference
price of 21 dollars. (OPEC-Oil Price)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
YANGON -- Myanmar is planning to build a new, modern and
international-level fish wholesale center in Myeik, southern
Tanintharyi division, to expand its sea fish and prawn market.
</P>
<P>
The center, to be set up by a local private company, will be
built on a 60.75-hectare plot, comprising of a jetty with an
investment of over 100 million U.S. dollars. (Myanmar-Firsh-
Center)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The International Monetary Fund (IMF) said on
Monday that it had agreed with Brazil on a new economic program
that would release 4.9 billion U.S. dollars for Brazil after an
executive board vote expected within weeks.
</P>
<P>
IMF Managing Director Michel Camdessus said he would recommend
to the IMF's executive board the approval of the revised program
for 1999-2001 proposed by the Brazilian government, which sees a
sharp drop in growth this year as well as falling inflation and
interest rates.(IMF-Brazil-Loans)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
HANOI -- Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam's largest economic hub, is
determined to post a 6-7 percent increase in exports this year
despite the economic slowdown, official media here reported
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
