<HEADLINE> NPC Enhances Overseas Contact </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 9 (Xinhua) -- The Ninth National People's
Congress (NPC) sent delegations to 24 countries and received
parliamentary delegations from 36 countries and international
parliamentary organizations last year.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Chunyun, vice-chairman of the NPC Standing Committee,
said here today that NPC also sent delegations to Parliament
European Commission and to attend ten international meetings last
year.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remarks in a report on the work of the NPC
Standing Committee at the ongoing Second Session of the Ninth NPC
here today.
</P>
<P>
He said that parliamentary diplomacy is an important part of
the diplomatic work of the country.
</P>
<P>
"It has flexible forms, wide contact areas and great influence,
" he said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that NPC successfully hosted the sixth annual session
of the Asia-Pacific Parliamentarians' Assembly on Environment and
Development in Guilin in southwest China's Guangxi province last
October.
</P>
<P>
He said that NPC is to continue to expand contact and exchanges
with foreign parliaments and parliamentarians. It will further
strengthen friendly cooperation with parliaments of China's
neighboring countries, expand relations with parliaments of
countries in Latin America and Africa, consistently improve and
enhance contacts with the parliaments of the United States and
European Union nations.
</P>
<P>
It will also play a greater role in multi-lateral diplomacy
through active participation in activities of international
parliamentary organizations such as Inter-Parliamentary Union and
Asia-Pacific Parliamentary Forum, he added.
</P>
<P>
"We will seek to achieve practical results in contact with
foreign parliaments so as to create a more favorable international
environment for China's reform, opening up and modernization drive,
" he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
