<HEADLINE> NPC Session Convenes Third Plenary Meeting (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"The three existing contracts laws have made significant
contributions to safeguarding the legal rights and interests of
the parties involved in the contract, maintaining social and
economic order, promoting economic growth, technological
advancement and expansion of foreign economic and trade affairs,
and guaranteeing smooth progress of the cause of socialist
construction," Gu said.
</P>
<P>
However, he pointed out that as China continues reforms and
opens wider to the outside world, the regulating scopes and some
rules of the three laws are no longer compatible with new economic
and social development.
</P>
<P>
The draft contracts law tabled today has an enlarged regulating
scope comparing with that of the three previous contracts laws, he
noted.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with a decision by the NPC Standing Committee, He
Chunlin, secretary-general of the NPC Standing Committee,
explained on the draft method for electing Ninth NPC deputies in
the Macao SAR.
</P>
<P>
The draft stipulates that the Macao SAR, which will be founded
after China resumes its exercise of sovereignty over Macao on
December 20 of this year, can have 12 deputies to the Ninth NPC.
</P>
<P>
Entrusted by the NPC Standing Committee to report its work over
the past year, Jiang Chunyun, vice-chairman of the NPC Standing
Committee, said that the NPC and its Standing Committee have made
painstaking efforts to strengthen legislation, improve the quality
of laws, enhance supervision on government work and law
enforcement, and promote exchanges and cooperation with foreign
parliaments and international organizations.
</P>
<P>
"In the coming year, the NPC Standing Committee will continue
to hold high the great banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory, regard
developing socialist democracy and legal system as its fundamental
task, and earnestly fulfill and exercise various functions and
powers bestowed by the Constitution, so as to promote the process
of governing the country according to law and building a socialist
country based on a rule of law," he added.
</P>
<P>
Members of the Ninth National Committee of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), China's top advisory
body which is also convening its second annual session in Beijing,
attended today's meeting as observers.  
</P>
