<DOCNO> XIE19990309.0297 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NPC Session Convenes Third Plenary Meeting (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
On January 22 this year, the CPC Central Committee formally
delivered its proposal on constitutional amendment to the NPC
Standing Committee. The latter discussed the proposal at its
seventh meeting and, in accordance with the stipulation of Article
64 of the Constitution, put forth a draft amendment, which has
been submitted to the ongoing NPC full session for deliberation.
</P>
<P>
The draft amendment suggests six major changes to the current
Chinese Constitution. To be written into the Constitution are: "
Deng Xiaoping Theory" as the country's guiding principle; the
principle of "governing the country according to law and building
a socialist country based on the rule of law;" "the State in a
primary stage of socialism shall adhere to the fundamental
economic system of taking public ownership as the mainstay and
promoting common development for economic sectors of multiple
ownerships, and to a distribution system where distribution
according to work is the main form and a co-existence of multiple
ways of distribution is allowed;" "rural collective economic
organizations shall adopt a double-deck operation system based on
household contract operation and on a combination of unified and
separate operations;" private economic entities existing and
developing "within the limits of law" should be regarded as "
important components of a socialist market economy;" and the term
of "counter-revolutionary activities" in the current Constitution
be abandoned and the concept of "criminal activities endangering
state security" be adopted.
</P>
<P>
Gu Angran, chairman of the Commission of Legislative Affairs
under the NPC Standing Committee, made expositions on the draft
contracts law according to a decision by the NPC Standing
Committee.
</P>
<P>
He said that guidelines for drafting the contracts law are to
draft a unified and relatively comprehensive contracts law by
proceeding from China's real conditions and absorbing useful
international experience under the guidance of Deng Xiaoping
Theory so as to guarantee a healthy development of the socialist
market economy.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, efforts must be made to maintain coherence and
consistency of the law, which has been formulated on the basis of
three existing laws, namely Economic Contracts Law, Law on
Economic Contracts involving Foreign Interests and Law on
Technological Contracts, said Gu.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
