<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NPC Standing Committee Improves Supervisory Role </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 9 (Xinhua) -- The Standing Committee of the
Ninth National People's Congress (NPC) improved its supervisory
work and increased the effectiveness of supervision last year,
Jiang Chunyun, vice-chairman of the committee said here today.
</P>
<P>
In delivering a work report to the ongoing NPC session, Jiang
said the NPC Standing Committee examined and inspected law
enforcement by organizing six inspection groups, hearing and
examining five work reports submitted by the State Councial and
departments under it, hearing and examining work reports by the
Supreme People's Court and Supreme People's Procuratorate, and
setting up a special institution for strengthened supervision over
budget implementation.
</P>
<P>
"The committee embodied its support for government work in its
supervisory work," the vice-chairman said. "It has supported and
urged the State Council and its departments, the Supreme People's
Court and Supreme People's Procuratorate to improve their work in
accordance with Law."
</P>
<P>
Jiang said the committee has strengthened supervision over the
implementation of the central budget in particular. It has decided
to set up a budget work subcommittee to improve supervision over
budget implementation and combat rampant irregularities in the
appropriation of fiscal fund.
</P>
<P>
In playing its supervisory role, the committee has focused on
major problems in economic and social development and problems
that attract the loudest complaints from people to ensure full
implementation of major decisions by the central authorities,
Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Special committees of the NPC also assisted the NPC Standing
Committee in exercising supervision, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
The vice-chairman pointed out that the NPC Standing Committee
will continue to tighten and improve supervision intended to
enable administrative, judicial and procuratorial bodies to do a
better job. Lax law enforcement remains a serious problem in China,
he said.
</P>
<P>
He added that the committee will continue to hear from state
administrative, judicial and procuratorial bodies reports on
important issues in reform and development and problems of common
concern, and increase supervision through investigations and
hearings over major cases reported by people.
</P>
<P>
Also, the committee is drafting a Law of Supervision and some
special supervision-related decisions, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
