<HEADLINE> Poisonous Liquor Kills 33 in Brazil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, March 8 (Xinhua) -- At least 33 people have
died due to drinking illegally-distilled alcohol in Brazil's
northeastern state of Bahia, police said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The three most recent deaths were registered last Sunday and
the number of fatalities is expected to rise in the next few days.
Police said the liquor was contaminated with methanol, a toxic
substance.
</P>
<P>
Federal police were hunting a man named Carlos Almeida, the
owner of the liquor factory, while two other suspects were
arrested. Officers also seized more than 5,000 liters of the
liquor. 
