<HEADLINE> OPEC Oil Price on New Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, March 8 (Xinhua) -- The average OPEC oil basket price
rose to 10.44 U.S. dollars per barrel last week from 10.17 dollars
in the previous week, as showed by statistics released here Monday
by the Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC).
</P>
<P>
The average OPEC oil price in February stood at 10.02 dollars
per barrel, down 0.72 dollars compared with 10.74 dollars in
January, and also lower than the average price of 12.28 dollars
last year and 18.68 dollars in 1997 as well as the OPEC reference
price of 21 dollars.
</P>
<P>
As the oil reserves of the United States and other major oil
consuming nations have declined recently and the OPEC members and
some non-OPEC countries are reported to seek ways to prevent oil
prices from diving, oil prices on the international market have
gained slightly.
</P>
<P>
The cold weather in the United States and Europe have also
contributed to fuel price hikes.
</P>
<P>
However, market analysts are uncertain whether oil prices will
maintain the rising trend. 
</P>
</TEXT>
