<HEADLINE> Myanmar to Build Modern Fish Wholesale Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, March 9 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar is planning to build a new,
modern and international-level fish wholesale center in Myeik,
southern Tanintharyi division, to expand its sea fish and prawn
market.
</P>
<P>
The center, to be set up by a local private company, will be
built on a 60.75-hectare plot, comprising of a jetty with an
investment of over 100 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar is boosting its fish and prawn production by also
allowing joint venture operation between the government and
private and foreign entrepreneurs.
</P>
<P>
There were altogether 3,065 hectares of fish and prawn breeding
ponds in Myanmar with an output of 6,357 tons in the 1990-91
fiscal year. The figures went up to 40,680 hectares of ponds with
a total output of 91,117 tons in the 1997-98 fiscal year. 
</P>
