<HEADLINE> Philippine Govt to Confiscate More Marcos Properties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 9, (Xinhua) -- The Philippine Bureau of Internal
Revenue (BIR) will confiscate 21 other properties of the Marcoses
as payment for their huge tax debts of 23.5 billion pesos (587.5
million U.S. Dollars), a newspaper reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Journal quoted sources from the BIR and the Supreme Court as
saying the formal Notice of Levy (seizure order) of these
properties have already been served.
</P>
<P>
The total land area of these 21 Marcos properties, which
included the family's ancestral home, mansions, condominium units,
private resorts and beaches is 89,425 square meters or 8.9425
hectares.
</P>
<P>
This is on top of the first 13 Tacloban, Leyte properties of
the Marcoses, which were earlier seized and are now in the custody
of the government.
</P>
<P>
Last week, the Supreme Court affirmed with finality its 1997
decision against the Marcoses in their tax liability case,
rejecting the efforts of the Marcoses to recover parcels of land
on which they have been assessed 23.47 billion pesos in unpaid
estate and income taxes. 
</P>
