<HEADLINE>   Seles Upset in Indian Wells Third Round </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 8 (Xinhua) -- Third seed Monica Seles of the
United States was eliminated by Slovakia's Henrieta Nagyova in the
third round of the 1.25 million-dollar WTA Tour Evert Cup in
Indian Wells on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Nagyova, ranked 27th in the world, needed just one hour and
five minutes to beat Seles 6-2, 6-4 and reach the quarter-finals.
</P>
<P>
"My mind definitely wasn't there from the start until the end,"
Seles said. "She didn't give me a chance really to get into it."
</P>
<P>
Seles was making her first appearance in the tournament since
1992, when she won the singles title.
</P>
<P>
Eighth-seeded Nathalie Tauziat upset by fellow Frenchwoman
Sandrine Testud 7-6 (7/3), 6-2 in one hour and 14 minutes.
</P>
<P>
It was the fourth day of play in the Evert Cup, and the first
day of play in the men's Champions Cup, the first of the ATP
Tour's prestigious Super Nine events of 1999.
</P>
<P>
Big serving Briton Greg Rusedski dispatched Czech Petr Korda 6-
3, 6-4 in the first round, blasting 11 aces.
</P>
<P>
Andre Agassi, forced to retire from his Scottsdale semi-final
last week with a pulled right hamstring, withdrew from the
Champions Cup. 
