<HEADLINE> Government Work Report Draws Favorable Response </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 9 (Xinhua) -- Premier Zhu Rongji's government
work report delivered at the ongoing session of the Ninth National
People's Congress has drawn favorable responses throughout the
country.
</P>
<P>
Many interviewed by Xinhua agree that the report is pragmatic,
seeks truth from facts and is encouraging, and that the national
economic growth rate for this year set in the report is feasible.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Yiren, a vice mayor of Shanghai, said that what this
largest industrial city in China has achieved in recent years
proves that the central government's policy to turn around money-
losing state-owned enterprises before the end of the century is
correct.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, Shanghai has reduced the averaged
debt rate of industrial enterprises to 54 percent and the
workforce of local state enterprises to 850,000 people, while a
social security system, medical insurance and pension insurance
for retirees have been established and developed in the city.
</P>
<P>
Cao Banggong, a senior engineer from Beijing, said he is deeply
touched by what the premier said about the government's financial
policy: "Implementing a proactive financial policy does not mean
that we can spend money freely; rather, we should treasure and be
economical about people's sweat money."
</P>
<P>
Zhang Baofeng, a woman laid off from a Beijing-based state
factory, said that the government work report gives priority to
raising funds for providing a basic living standard guarantee for
workers laid off from state enterprises and to their re-employment.
"This is exactly we are thinking about," she said.
</P>
<P>
"We should also change our views on employment, changing the
attitude of being not willing to do dirty and hard work," she said.
</P>
<P>
The government work report is also assuring for Huang Shihe, a
local farmer in Chengdu, capital of Sichuan province. "The premier
has promised to continue the Party's basic rural policy and I'm
completely reassured," said the farmer who bought a mobile phone
after hearing Zhu's report on television.
</P>
<P>
Huang said he will sell his vegetables produced in greenhouses
to other parts of the country.
</P>
<P>
The government work report has also won appreciation from
university teachers and scientists as well as people living in
areas inhabited mainly by ethnic minorities.. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
