<HEADLINE> El Salvador Wins Davis Cup Elimination Round </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, March 8 (Xinhua) -- El Salvador and Guatemala
advanced to the second division of the Davis Cup, taking the top
two places in an American Zone elimination round.
</P>
<P>
"We've been fighting for this for two years," El Salvador
captain Roberto Salazar said Sunday after his team swept the
singles matches en route to a 2-1 victory over Guatemala.
</P>
<P>
Yari Bernardo beat Alex Lehnhoff 4-6, 6-2, 6-4, and Manuel
Tejada beat Daniel Chavez 6-4, 6-4, 6-3. In doubles, Guatemalans
Lehnhoff and Luis Valencia beat Jose Baires and Augusto Sanabria 6-
4, 6-3.
</P>
