<HEADLINE> China Loses Opener in World Ice Hockey Pool A </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, March 8 (Xinhua) -- China has a disappointing opener
when it was beaten by Sweden 1-3 in the Pool A Ice Hockey World
Championship in Helsinki, Finland on Monday.
</P>
<P>
With five minutes into the game, China conceded the first goal
and the second six minutes later in the first period.
</P>
<P>
China managed scored its first goal in the second period but
could not keep up the pace due to fatigue and rusty skills in the
third period.
</P>
<P>
It was a cheerful revenge for Sweden as it was beaten by China
3-1 in the Nagano Olympic Games last year.
</P>
<P>
The retirement of some veterans and the lack of experiences
contributed most to the failure of the Chinese squad, said Chinese
team officials.
</P>
<P>
In other matches of the day, the United States whitewashed
Russia 10-2, Canada dumped Switzerland 10-0, Finland nipped
Germany 9-0.
</P>
<P>
The eight teams were first pitched into two groups with top two
teams from each group advancing to the finals.
</P>
<P>
The last-placed squad will be relegated to Pool B. 
</P>
