<HEADLINE> Italy, Czech Republic Claims Victory in Sprint Relays </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, March 8 (Xinhua) -- The Italian men's second team
stormed home to win over Estonia, while the Czech Republic women's
team claimed the title in the World Cup cross country skiing
sprint relays in Vantaa, Finland on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Italians Giorgio di Centa and Christian Zorzi, each skiing
every other two-kilometer leg, edged Estonia's Pavo Raudsepp and
Meelis Aalsmae by 1.1 seconds, with Zorzi taking the finish.
</P>
<P>
Italy's first team of Silvio Fauner and Pietro Piller Cottrer
was 3.1 seconds behind the winner in a relay.
</P>
<P>
The Czech Republic duo of Katerina Neumannova and Katerina
Hanusova led the rest of the field from the start of 12 kilometers
women's relay, and their winning time was 18.6 seconds faster than
their nearest French rivals Annick Pierrel and Karine Philippot.
</P>
<P>
Switzerland's Sylvia Honecker and Brigitte Albrecht finished
third with a time of further 3.5 seconds behind. 
</P>
